Write a function indexOfValue that takes a non-empty arr array and value as arguments
and returns the index of the array element with value or undefined if there is no such element.

Example:

indexOfValue ([1, 3, 6, 2, 6], 6)  must return 2;
indexOfValue ([0, 1, 2], 5) must return undefined;
indexOfValue ([4, 1, 1, 2], 1)  must return 1.

Solution:

function indexOfValue(arr, value){
 return arr.indexOf(value) !== -1 ? arr.indexOf(value) : undefined;
}
